<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-85-0169 </DOCNO><TEXT>We consider in the highly conducting half-space an x-invariant arcadeforce-free field which is evolving in a quasi-static way as a consequenceof a velocity field imposed on a boundary plane. We show in particularthat, when the shear exceeds a critical value, the configuration becomesmetastable whith respect to non-linear perturbations which change thetopology of the field lines, but preserve the magnetic fluxes.</TEXT></DOC>